DevSecOps is a development practice that integrates security initiatives at every stage of the software development lifecycle. The goal is to deliver robust and secure applications. 
DevSecOps stands for: Development, Security, Operations. 
DevSecOps includes tools and processes that encourage collaboration between: Developers, Security specialists, Operation teams. 
DevSecOps automates the integration of security at every phase of the software development lifecycle, from: Initial design, Integration, Testing, Deployment, Software delivery. 
DevSecOps includes: 
API security testing
Cloud and container security
Open source security and license management
Malicious code detection
M&A due diligence
Quality and security standards compliance
